			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> paper:</span><br><i>Towards an Incremental Update Approach for Concrete Textual Syntaxes for UUID-Based Model Repositories</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ThomasGoldschmidt.html">Thomas Goldschmidt</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_11">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_11</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagM">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> It proposes incremental updating to keep models and concrete textual syntaxes in sync during ongoing edits/maintenance.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It discusses (and motivates) tooling/framework support for incremental parsing and model updates.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The core challenge is integration between textual concrete syntax and UUID-based model repositories.
</li></ul></li></ul>
